text: Utajärvi is a municipality in Northern Ostrobothnia, Finland. As of 31 December 2023, 2,492 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Muhos, Oulu, Pudasjärvi, Puolanka and Vaala. Utajärvi was founded in 1865. The wooden church was built in 1762. The popular rock band 22-Pistepirkko was founded in Utajärvi in 1980. == Other websites == * Municipality of Utajärvi – Official website Category:Municipalities of North Ostrobothnia Category:1865 establishments in Finland
